OL,3,CAs Royal Mail issues warning over
OL,4,Ccounterfeit stamps, how do you spot a
OL,5,Cfake?
OL,7,F"We want our customers to buy stamps
OL,8,Fwith confidence. We strongly recommend
OL,9,Fthat customers only purchase stamps
OL,10,Ffrom Post Offices and other reputable
OL,11,FHigh Street retailers, and not to buy
OL,12,Fstamps online ` unless from the
OL,13,Fofficial Royal Mail shop."
OL,15,F"Our website provides customers with
OL,16,Fguidance on how to spot counterfeit or
OL,17,Fused stamps and we urge customers to
OL,18,Freport any suspicious stamps to Royal
OL,19,FMail via our so that we can
OL,20,Finvestigate.
